bug.short_desc: Drag and drop does not work in Safari 5.2.1

long_desc.thetext:
Currently in qooxdoo 4.0 drag and drop do not works in safari, I found this problem when test my application in safari.
Reference link: http://demo.qooxdoo.org/devel/demobrowser/#ui~DragDrop.html http://demo.qooxdoo.org/current/showcase/#Drag%20%26%20Drop Due to this problem, these 2 demos does not work in safari
This is really critical, please check it! Thanks very much!

Just checked both demos and the work as expected. But I recently fixed (#8447) the min drag distance which was 50px and with that too much. Maybe that cause some confusion. If it is still not working with the newest master, feel free to reopen and we figure out how to reproduce the issue.
Created attachment 1329 demo drag and drop issue
Created attachment 1330 show case drag and drop issue

(In reply to comment #1) > Just checked both demos and the work as expected. But I recently fixed (#8447) > the min drag distance which was 50px and with that too much. Maybe that cause > some confusion. If it is still not working with the newest master, feel free to > reopen and we figure out how to reproduce the issue.
Hello Martin,
Thanks for your reply!
I've checked demo and show case this morning, still do not work in safari, drop position always stay on top left corner (attached pics for your reference).
Currently I'm using 4.0, I haven't yet try with latest master, but from my point of view, if these issues still happen in show case and demo in safari, then they're not resolved.
BTW, my safari version is 5.1.2.
I've checked framework drag.js implementation, it seems getDocumentLeft and getDocumentTop method do not get correct position.

@Martin,
I've checked what you changed in DragDrop.js and replace my local DragDrop.js with the file changed, but the problem is still there.
So I'm sure now it's not resolved. Maybe we can have a discussion this afternoon(morning on your time), then I can directly show you this issue. My skype id is jianyou.yao, feel free to contact me.
Thanks for your help!

Oh, you are talking of Safari 5.x. I'm sorry to disappoint you but we dropped the support for Safari < 6 with 3.5 version as you can see in the manual: http://manual.qooxdoo.org/current/pages/desktop/requirements.html

(In reply to comment #6) > Oh, you are talking of Safari 5.x. I'm sorry to disappoint you but we dropped > the support for Safari < 6 with 3.5 version as you can see in the manual: > http://manual.qooxdoo.org/current/pages/desktop/requirements.html
I'm confused now, from the official document, safari 3+ is supported in qooxdoo 3.5.1, reference http://manual.qooxdoo.org/3.5.x/pages/website/requirements.html, but now you told me safari < 6 in qooxdoo 3.5 is not supported.
Which one is corrected? And in qooxdoo 4.0, also safari 6+ is supported from the link you given to me.

(In reply to comment #6) > Oh, you are talking of Safari 5.x. I'm sorry to disappoint you but we dropped > the support for Safari < 6 with 3.5 version as you can see in the manual: > http://manual.qooxdoo.org/current/pages/desktop/requirements.html
Sorry, What I've checked is website, for desktop is http://manual.qooxdoo.org/3.5.x/pages/desktop/requirements.html
so I think all the description is correct! Thanks very much!
